The angular resolution $\theta$ of a single dish can be calculated using the formula:
$$
\theta = \frac{1.22 \lambda}{D}
$$
where $\lambda$ is the wavelength and $D$ is the diameter of the dish. Substituting the given values:
$$
\theta = \frac{1.22 \times 1 \mathrm{~cm}}{1 \mathrm{~m}} = \frac{1.22 \times 10^{-2} \mathrm{~m}}{1 \mathrm{~m}} = 1.22 \times 10^{-2} \mathrm{~radians}
$$
So, the angular resolution of a single dish is $1.22 \times 10^{-2}$ radians.

