Using Kirchoff Current Law at the node between the inductor and capacitor with the assumed currents both positive into the node gives the following:
\[
\begin{gathered}
i_{L}+i_{C}=0 \\
i_{L}=\frac{1}{L} \int v_{L} d t \\
i_{C}=C \frac{d v_{c}}{d t}
\end{gathered}
